Running a Vanilla ChromiumOS VM in Virtualbox
NOTE: This method uses an older outdated version of ChromiumOS

Open a web browser and download the ChromiumOS .ova Download
Extract the downloaded .zip file
Launch VirtualBox
Create a New VM by selecting Machine > New
Name: ChromiumOS
Machine Folder: C:\VMs
Type: Linux
Version: Other Linux (32-bit)
Memory Size: 2048 MB
Hard disk: Use an existing virtual hard disk now

Click the folder icon > Browse to and select the extracted ChromeOS-Vanilla .vdi file
Click Create
Select the VM and Click Settings
Select System > Processor
Check the Enable PAE/NX checkbox
Select Display
Slide the Video Memory to 128 MB
Select Network
Set the attached to dropdown to Bridged Adapter
Expand the Advanced options area
Set the Adapter Type to Intel PRO/1000 MT Desktop
Click OK
Make sure the ChromiumOS VM is selected and click Start > Normal
Click Continue on the Welcome! screen
Press Escape to cancel checking for updates
Click the browse as guest link
Welcome to ChromiumOS
 
